               <p>ANN MANNOX. I am <rs id="t18281023-238-viclabel1385" type="occupation">single</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-238-victim1256 t18281023-238-viclabel1385"></join> - I was in the service of Mr. Deacon, of <placeName id="t18281023-238-crimeloc1386">St. John's-street-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-238-crimeloc1386" type="placeName" value="St. John's-street-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18281023-238-crimeloc1386" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18281023-238-off1383 t18281023-238-crimeloc1386"></join>. The prisoner was employed there half a day on the 24th of September - I took the breakfast up stairs about a quarter to nine o'clock, and stopped to make a bed, leaving him in the back kitchen; I came down in a quarter of an hour, and he was gone - I missed a sovereign in about two hours from a box in the back kitchen; it was locked, but the key was in another box - my clothes, and about 3l. 10s. in silver were on the box; I saw him next morning in custody - his mother asked how he came to take my sovereign - he said he was very sorry, and that he had changed it of a man at the canal, who he bought some fishing things of.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18281023-238-person1257">
                  CHARLES 
                  HERDSFIELD
               <interp inst="t18281023-238-person1257" type="surname" value="HERDSFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-238-person1257" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18281023-238-person1257" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 24th of September I saw the prisoner in Mr. Rhodes' brick-field, with a fishing-rod, a can and bag - he said, "See what I have found;" I said, "Don't tell stories, the lady has been to your mother, and says you have stolen it" - he then said he had found the sovereign, and told me to tell nobody.</p>
